      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/hemolysis-bench-comparison-01",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index comparison against published pump registry data",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values from the CFD model were compared against hemolysis measurements drawn from a multi-centre pump registry. The registry data span 47 implant centres and cover the same five flow-speed operating points specified in the COU. Agreement within ±18% was observed at all operating points, and the Monte Carlo 95th-percentile band encompassed all registry observations. The assessment team treated this comparison as equivalent to a controlled bench experiment because the operating conditions were tightly specified in the registry protocol and patient selection criteria were standardised. Consequently, the team concluded that the validation evidence satisfies the controlled-experiment requirement stated in the verification plan.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
