      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification coverage check",
      "description": "5000-sample Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition uncertainty and blood viscosity variability through the hemolysis sub-model. The 95th-percentile predicted NIH remained below the clinical threshold of 0.01 g/100 L at all five operating points. Coverage of the registry observations within the MC band was used as a secondary validation metric.",
